<section class="hero wrap">
  <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>TDS &middot; Section 201(1A)</span>
  <h1>TDS Interest <span class="grad-text">Calculator</span></h1>
  <p class="answer-first"><b>Interest under Section 201(1A) is 1% per month for late deduction (from the date tax was deductible to the date deducted) and 1.5% per month for late deposit (from the date deducted to the date deposited).</b> Any part of a calendar month is treated as a full month.</p>
</section>

<div class="panel-wrap">
  <div class="calc-panel">
    <div class="field"><label>TDS amount (Rs.)</label><input type="number" id="amt" placeholder="e.g. 100000"></div>
    <div class="field"><label>Nature of default</label>
      <select id="rate"><option value="1.5">Late deposit &mdash; 1.5% per month [201(1A)(ii)]</option><option value="1">Late deduction &mdash; 1% per month [201(1A)(i)]</option></select></div>
    <div class="row2"><div class="field"><label>From date (deductible / deducted)</label><input type="date" id="d1"></div>
      <div class="field"><label>To date (deducted / deposited)</label><input type="date" id="d2"></div></div>
    <div class="field"><div class="hint">Part of a month counts as a full month. The month count spans the calendar months touched between the two dates.</div></div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" style="width:100%;margin-top:6px" onclick="calc()">Calculate interest</button>
    <div id="out"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose" style="padding-top:30px">
    <h2>How TDS interest is computed</h2>
    <p>Interest = TDS &times; Rate &times; Months. The number of months is counted treating <b>any part of a month as a full month</b>. For late <i>deposit</i>, courts and the department count from the month of deduction to the month of payment &mdash; so even one day's delay across a month boundary can mean two months' interest.</p>
    <div class="callout law"><b>Section 201(1A), Income-tax Act</b> &mdash; 1% p.m. for failure to deduct [201(1A)(i)]; 1.5% p.m. for failure to deposit after deduction [201(1A)(ii)].</div>
    <div class="callout warn"><b>Caution.</b> The interest month is a calendar-month-of-deduction to month-of-deposit count, not 30-day periods. This tool counts the calendar months touched. ✓ Section 201(1A) rates: 1%/month (late deduction), 1.5%/month (late deposit). Verified June 2026. the exact month count for borderline dates.</div>
    <div class="faq"><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <details><summary>Is interest on TDS allowed as a business expense?</summary><p>No. Interest under Section 201(1A) on late deduction or deposit of TDS is not deductible as business expenditure.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Does the 1.5% run from the date of deduction or the due date of deposit?</summary><p>From the date of deduction to the date of actual deposit &mdash; not from the deposit due date. This is why delays are computed from the deduction month.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Is interest different under the Income-tax Act, 2025?</summary><p>The interest mechanism for TDS defaults continues; map the relevant new-Act provision once notified. ✓ Section 201(1A): 1%/month late deduction, 1.5%/month late deposit. Verified June 2026.</p></details>
    </div>
    <div class="key-takeaways"><h2>Key takeaways</h2><ul>
      <li>1% p.m. for late deduction; 1.5% p.m. for late deposit.</li>
      <li>Part of a month = full month (calendar-based).</li>
      <li>Late-deposit interest runs from the date of deduction.</li>
      <li>Section 201(1A) interest is not a deductible expense.</li>
    </ul></div>
